	<exercise>
	<title>Simplifying Rational Expressions</title>
	<statement>
		<p>Simplify each expression. Assume <m>x</m> is a non-zero real number.</p>
		<ol labels="a" cols="6">
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{1}{\frac{1}{x}}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{x}{\frac{1}{x}}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{1}{\frac{x}{x}}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{1}{\frac{x}{1}}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{x}{\frac{x}{1}}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{x}{\frac{x}{x}}</m></li>
		</ol>
	</statement>
	</exercise>

	<exercise>
	<title>Avoiding Common Mistakes</title>
	<statement>
		<p>Is <m>\displaystyle \frac{z}{x+y}</m> the same as <m>\displaystyle \frac{z}{x}+\frac{z}{y}</m>? Is <m>\displaystyle \frac{x+y}{z}</m> the same as <m>\displaystyle \frac{x}{z}+\frac{y}{z}</m>?</p>
	</statement>
	</exercise>


	<exercise>
	<title>Expanding Products</title>
	<statement>
		<p>Multiply and simplify your final answers.
			<ol marker="a" cols="2">
				<li><m>(x+y)^3</m></li>
				<li><m>x(x-y)^2</m></li>
				<li><m>(\sqrt{2}-3)(\sqrt{2}+3)</m></li>
				<li><m>(\sqrt{4x^2+1}-2x)(\sqrt{4x^2+1}+2x)</m></li>
			</ol></p>
	</statement>
	<answer>
		<ol marker="a" >
				<li><m>(x+y)^3 = x^3+3 x^2 y+3 x y^2+y^3</m></li>
				<li><m>x(x-y)^2 = x^3-2 x^2 y+x y^2</m></li>
				<li><m>(\sqrt{2}-3)(\sqrt{2}+3) =  -7</m></li>
				<li><m>(\sqrt{4x^2+1}-2x)(\sqrt{4x^2+1}+2x) = 1</m></li>
		</ol>
	</answer>
	</exercise>
	

	<exercise>
	<title>Addition and Subtraction with Rational Expressions</title>
	<statement>
		<p>Perform the indicated addition or subtraction and simplify the expression as much as possible. Show your work carefully as a sequence of equal expressions seperated with the equal sign.</p>
		<ol labels="a" cols="2">
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{2x}{5} - \frac{2}{x+4}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{2}{5x} + \frac{2}{x+4}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{x+4}{x^2-4}-\frac{x-1}{x-2}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{2}{x}+\frac{x-1}{x^2+1}</m></li>
		</ol>
	</statement>
	<answer>
		<ol labels="a" >
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{2x}{5} - \frac{2}{x+4} = \frac{2 \left(x^2+4 x-5\right)}{5 (x+4)}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{2}{5x} + \frac{2}{x+4} = \frac{4 (3 x+2)}{5 x (x+4)}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{x+4}{x^2-4}-\frac{x-1}{x-2} = \frac{6-x^2}{(x-2) (x+2)}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{2}{x}+\frac{x-1}{x^2+1} = \frac{3 x^2-x+2}{x \left(x^2+1\right)}</m></li>
		</ol>
	</answer>
	</exercise>

	<exercise>
	<title>Multiplication and Division with Rational Expressions</title>
	<statement>
		<p>Perform the indicated multplication or division and simplify the expression as much as possible. Show your work carefully as a sequence of equal expressions seperated with the equal sign.</p>
		<ol labels="a" cols="2">
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{2x}{5} \cdot \frac{2}{x+4}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{2x}{5} \div \frac{2}{x+4}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{x+4}{x^2-4}\cdot\frac{x-1}{x-2}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{x+4}{x^2-4}\div\frac{x-1}{x-2}</m></li>
		</ol>
	</statement>
	<answer>
		<ol labels="a">
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{2x}{5} \cdot \frac{2}{x+4} = \frac{4 x}{5 (x+4)} = \frac{4x}{5x+20}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{2x}{5} \div \frac{2}{x+4} = \frac{1}{5} x (x+4) = \frac{x^2+4x}{5}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{x+4}{x^2-4}\cdot\frac{x-1}{x-2} = \frac{(x-1) (x+4)}{(x-2)^2 (x+2)}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{x+4}{x^2-4}\div\frac{x-1}{x-2} = \frac{x+4}{x^2+x-2}</m></li>
		</ol>
	</answer>
	</exercise>

	<exercise>
	<title>Simplifying Compound Rational Expressions</title>
	<statement>
		<p>Simplify each expression as much as possible. Show your work carefully as a sequence of equal expressions seperated with the equal sign.</p>
		<ol labels="a">
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{\frac{3}{2x}}{\frac{1}{3x}}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{\frac{y}{x+y}+1}{x}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{\frac{1}{x}-\frac{1}{y}}{\frac{1}{x^2}+\frac{1}{y^2}}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{x+1-\frac{1}{x+1}}{\frac{x}{x+1}}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{1}{1+(y/x)^2}</m></li>
		</ol>
	</statement>
	<answer>
		<ol labels="a">
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{\frac{3}{2x}}{\frac{1}{3x}} = 9/2</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{\frac{y}{x+y}+1}{x} = \frac{x+2y}{x^2+xy}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{\frac{1}{x}-\frac{1}{y}}{\frac{1}{x^2}+\frac{1}{y^2}} = \frac{xy^2-x^2y}{x^2+y^2}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{x+1-\frac{1}{x+1}}{\frac{x}{x+1}} = 2+x</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{1}{1+(y/x)^2} = \frac{x^2}{x^2+y^2}</m></li>
		</ol>
	</answer>
	</exercise>

	<exercise>
	<title>Simplifying Radical Expressions</title>
	<statement>
		<p>Perform the indicated operation and simplify the expression as much as possible. Show your work carefully as a sequence of equal expressions seperated with the equal sign.</p>
		<ol labels="a" cols="2">
			<li>Subtract: <m>\displaystyle \frac{\sqrt{4+x^2}}{x}-\frac{x}{\sqrt{4+x^2}}</m></li>
			<li>Multiply: <m>\displaystyle \frac{\sqrt{4+x^2}-2}{x} \cdot \frac{\sqrt{4+x^2}+2}{\sqrt{4+x^2}+2}</m></li>
		</ol>
	</statement>
	<answer>
		<ol labels="a">
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{\sqrt{4+x^2}}{x}-\frac{x}{\sqrt{4+x^2}} = \frac{4}{x \sqrt{x^2+4}} </m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{\sqrt{4+x^2}-2}{x} \cdot \frac{\sqrt{4+x^2}+2}{\sqrt{4+x^2}+2} = \frac{x}{\sqrt{4+x^2}+2}</m></li>
		</ol>
	</answer>
	</exercise>

	<exercise>
		<title>Avoiding Common Mistakes</title>
		<statement>
			<p>Is <m>\sqrt{x^2}</m> the same as <m>x</m>? Is <m>\sqrt{4+x^2}</m> the same as <m>2+x</m>?  Is <m>\sqrt{4x^2}</m> the same as <m>2x</m>?</p>
